The upcoming Spring Batch v4.2 GA will provide support for reading/writing data to Apache Kafka topics. You can already try it out with the [4.2.0.RC1 release](https://docs.spring.io/spring-batch/4.2.x/reference/html/whatsnew.html#whatsNew).

For the `KafkaItemWriter`, you will need to configure a `KafkaTemplate`. Here is an example of the writer:

	@Bean
	public KafkaItemWriter&lt;String, Demo1&gt; kafkaItemWriter(KafkaTemplate&lt;String, Demo1&gt; kafkaTemplate) {
		return new KafkaItemWriterBuilder&lt;String, Demo1&gt;()
				.kafkaTemplate(kafkaTemplate)
				.build();
	}

You can also take a look at the [Spring Tips installment](https://spring.io/blog/2019/05/15/spring-tips-spring-batch-and-apache-kafka) about Kafka support in Spring Batch by Josh Long.

